description: Johan decides to enter a competition in Berkendael. The competition is disturbed by freedom fighters who want to overthrow the local lord who got to his throne dishonorably.
name: De Vrijschutter

description:
Johan is on his way to a friends wedding when he meets a giant called Baloch. The giant serves Verdal, an evil wizard, who corrupts the bride's sister against her.

English translation of the title: Baloch, the Giant.

Silver cover, with full color pages released in 1994.
name: Baloch, De Reus
Henry, roi de France et d'Angleterre

description:
A LEGENDARY SAGA FROM ARTHURIAN TIMES.

King Mark of Cornwall sees his realm invaded by Irish warriors. Unable to count on King Arthur, who is fi ghting off Pictish invaders, he can only rely on his most faithful servant, Rivalen de Loonois. In this war-ravaged country, Tristan, the son of Rivalen, grows up marked forever by his father’s tragic fate.
name: Le sang du Loonois

description:
TRISTAN AND ISOLDE MEET IN THE MIDST OF WAR AND TREACHERY…

Since the Hibernois triumphed and Rivalen of Loonois disappeared, the Cornwall has lost its soul. The Mark lords, one more feeble than the next, play spies for the great king Duncan. After eleven years spent in the heart of the forest, Tristan comes back to embrace his destiny. The orphan has become a man about to meet his legendary companion. But forget the Isolde you know…
name: La Filleule des Fées

description:
THE VAST KINGDOM OF EARTH’S SONS IS UNDER THREAT.

Its arch-enemy has reappeared – the Drekkars are emerging from the shadows after a ten centuries absence. Deep in the Passe, a sophisticated people have evolved, equipped with an ultra-codified hierarchical system. But when the Emperor pushes the Drekkars into all-out war against the outside world, dissenting voices are being heard...
name: Le chant d'Anoerer

description:
THE SECOND OPUS IN THE GREAT SAGA!

The vast kingdom of the Sons of the Earth is under threat. Its arch-enemy has reappeared – the Drekkars are emerging from the shadows after a ten-century-long absence. Deep in the Passe, a sophisticated people have evolved, equipped with an ultra-codified hierarchical system. But when the Emperor pushes the Drekkars into all-out war against the outside world, dissenting voices are heard...
name: Drekkars

description:
ALREADY A CULT SERIES!

The Powers are the first to populate the Earth. When Man appeared, he created among them passion and division. They will all take human form: Dragons, Giants, Angels, Sirens and Fairies. Then came the time for fights, internal wars...

A thousand years have gone by, and the Sons of the earth ended up creating the biggest of kingdoms. For them, the Powers are only legends anymore... But the Dragons came out of their lair...

A new age is coming: is it the end or the beginning of servitude?
name: L'Adieu aux Rois
Y a-t-il un geek pour sauver l'arène?

description:
The very unofficial parody of Peter Jackson’s new blockbuster!

An avalanche of jokes that neophytes and fans of Tolkien alike will enjoy!

A surprising adventure that will definitely remind you of another…

A parody to govern them all! A parody to find them.

A parody to bring them all and in the darkness unite them.

In the lands of the North where the serious Coron reigns!

WHAT IF ONE OF THE MAJOR RELIGIONS HAD NEVER EXISTED...

In the year 1213, Atlantis is discovered by sailors, holding many mysteries. For if a volcano didn’t destroy the city, what evil decimated the population? Two years later, France is touched by an evil curse brought back by these same sailors, soon nicknamed the Evil of souls. Alaric, young member of Missi Dominici, the messengers of the emperor, finds himself confronted with this epidemic that ravages the population, making its victims lose their minds.
name: Le Mal des Esprits

description:
AN OFFER YOU CAN’T REFUSE!

Here is an album that is unusual, delirious and fi lled with humor, halfway between a guide and a graphic novel, that introduces you all the things and tricks to become a figure in organized crime!

volume.name: Devenir Mafieux: Une Offre qu'on ne Peut pas Refuser

description:
LEON HAS SOME ARTISTIC TALENT....

...but at his mother’s death the young boy finds himself alone with his father, the village café owner, who doesn’t understand his son’s passion for drawing. in the forest, Leon meets a strange kind of guy, a painter and an hermit, who teaches him the basics of technique and a little art history. intense and exulting moments when Leon finally feels like himself. Leon entertains the dream of being able to live from it one day… but the war begins, turning upside down a still budding destiny…

volume.name: Du Vent Sous les Pieds Emporte Mes Pas
